                  <span class="">Both Friedrich Hayek and John Maynard Keynes have written approvingly of Mandevilleâ&euro;&trade;s fable. According to Hayek, Adam Smith gained insights into the division of labor, self-interest, economic liberty, and the idea of unintended consequences from Mandeville (Hayek 1984: 184â&euro;&ldquo;85). Keynes approved of Mandevilleâ&euro;&trade;s anti-saving sentiments and statist pressures to assure full employment in society (Key...</span>
